    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="429"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659a.119/14</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-22T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 23, 3.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10185. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 626. After several weeks conferences between Allied Governments and Iceland
                    delegates, at which I was present or represented, an agreement has been reached
                    between British, French and Italians on one side and Icelanders covering in
                    detail the points summarized below.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
